Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.62,0:00:16.46,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So there was nothing left behind that \Nwould help us identify the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.46,0:00:18.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Their motive was probably a grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.32,0:00:22.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They hit him once in the \Nhead with a metal pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.61,0:00:24.79,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You again, Mori-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.27,0:00:29.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I just happened to be passing by, \Nand it seemed like there was a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.96,0:00:33.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And this kid insisted we take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.80,0:00:39.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, are they the victim's \Nsurviving family members?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.53,0:00:40.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.80,0:00:43.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We had them come to confirm \Nthe identity of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.58,0:00:47.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}His mother Kadowaki Yasuko-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.06,0:00:47.48,Yasuko,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Kadowaki Yasuko (63) \NFormer Grade School Teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.69,0:00:50.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and his older brother Kadowaki Yuichi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.52,0:00:50.98,Yuichi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Kadowaki Yuichi (28) \NEldest Kadowaki Son \NGovernment Office Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.46,0:00:54.12,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, keep it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.92,0:00:57.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The father died five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.23,0:01:02.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The three of them were living together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.67,0:01:05.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right now at this moment, \Nlight pierces the darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.77,0:01:07.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Overcome all limits with \Nyour cool reasoning skills!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.72,0:01:09.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A chance encounter with \Nyet another assault case!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.55,0:01:11.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The surprising true face \Nof a troubled family!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.59,0:01:13.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.18,0:01:15.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.04,0:01:17.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:05.03,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(399,1)}The Mystery-Solving Water Taxi \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.59,0:03:02.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Mystery-Solving Water Taxi, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.05,0:03:11.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The victim was Kadowaki Eiji-san, twenty-three \Nyears old, who lives down the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.62,0:03:10.54,Eiji,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Kadowaki Eiji (23) \NKadowaki Second Son \NUnemployed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.19,0:03:14.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He was killed last night around ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.06,0:03:16.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,According to his mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.04,0:03:21.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,the victim went out to \Ndrink yesterday evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.97,0:03:26.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He was probably attacked on his way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.74,0:03:28.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So unaware of what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.57,0:03:32.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,his family was waiting for \Nthe victim to return home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.81,0:03:33.85,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.16,0:03:37.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, his older brother Yuichi-san \Nwas staying at a hotel in the city
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.95,0:03:40.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,to work on some documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.71,0:03:43.79,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently he works as an \Nofficial in Kasumigaseki.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.79,0:03:46.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,For the Chuo government office, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.34,0:03:48.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So he's an elite.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.12,0:03:52.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure! Oh, Mori-san and Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.45,0:03:54.42,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Well? How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.42,0:03:55.50,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.85,0:04:01.84,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The victim Kadowaki Eiji-san didn't have a \Nvery good reputation in the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.17,0:04:04.92,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Since he dropped out of \Ncollege three years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.92,0:04:08.56,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,he hasn't been able to hold down \Na job and wanders the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.89,0:04:14.56,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Last Friday, he got drunk and \Nargued with a bar employee.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.22,0:04:18.78,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He spent the night in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.43,0:04:22.73,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We also found two interesting \Npieces of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.73,0:04:24.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Which are?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.06,0:04:26.20,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The first is passers-by reported \Nthat several days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.58,0:04:32.26,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,a well-built man in his thirties appeared \Nto be watching the Kadowaki family,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.26,0:04:34.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,as though investigating them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.87,0:04:39.95,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He was also questioning the neighbors \Nabout the Kadowaki family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.95,0:04:43.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Considering the victim's reputation...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.06,0:04:49.12,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible he had some trouble \Nwith that man and incurred his wrath.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.12,0:04:50.85,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.17,0:04:54.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Keep trying to figure out who that man is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.32,0:04:54.97,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.33,0:04:59.82,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What's the other piece of information?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.82,0:05:00.36,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.91,0:05:05.23,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,According to the neighbors, it \Nseems the victim Kadowaki Eiji-san
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.23,0:05:09.49,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,was abusing his mother Yasuko-san daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.85,0:05:10.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.88,0:05:15.85,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, the older brother Yuichi-san
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.85,0:05:19.63,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,would always stop his brother's \Nexplosive violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.05,0:05:21.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:26.72,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So the victim was the problem \Nchild of the Kadowaki family.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.72,0:05:28.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.88,0:05:33.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That woman seems genuinely sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.31,0:05:37.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They say the worse a child is, \Nthe more you love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.83,0:05:38.96,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.96,0:05:41.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But if that's the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.31,0:05:47.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,we'll have to question \Nthe older brother again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.49,0:05:52.91,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,N-No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.09,0:05:56.13,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no domestic violence in our family!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.13,0:05:59.54,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,That's just an irresponsible rumor!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.85,0:06:04.55,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, what does that have \Nto do with Eiji's murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.02,0:06:12.46,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Kadowaki Yuichi-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.86,0:06:17.81,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but could we \Ntalk to you at the station?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.78,0:06:23.69,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You think I killed Eiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.97,0:06:28.71,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,N-No! Yuichi would never do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.71,0:06:30.49,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I just tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.49,0:06:32.38,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I was working all last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.38,0:06:35.16,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Please calm down, Kadowaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.38,0:06:40.04,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I know. Around ten, I ran \Ninto a woman at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.95,0:06:43.29,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,She was extremely drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.51,0:06:48.60,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, find her.\NThen this will all become clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.67,0:06:53.53,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,No. Yuichi would never...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.68,0:07:00.19,Station,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,MPD Beika Police Station
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.07,0:07:00.19,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.50,0:07:04.57,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I would never do something \Nas stupid as kill a person!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:09.45,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So, what about \NEiji-san's domestic violence?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.80,0:07:12.55,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,It's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.55,0:07:16.09,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Your father died five years ago, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.09,0:07:17.45,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.11,0:07:24.33,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,According to your neighbors, your mother \Nhas been frequently injured since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.63,0:07:26.84,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.10,0:07:31.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And two years later, Eiji-san \Ndropped out of college.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.76,0:07:37.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You managed to protect your mother until then, \Nbut after that, you couldn't handle it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.65,0:07:38.85,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,This is nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.10,0:07:42.79,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, you've been \Nbusy with work lately,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.79,0:07:46.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,so you've been out of the house a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.86,0:07:51.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And around that same time, your mother's \Ninjuries became more frequent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.14,0:07:53.86,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.13,0:07:57.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,If you didn't do something about Eiji,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.62,0:08:00.87,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,he might do something \Nthat couldn't be undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.10,0:08:03.55,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.09,0:08:07.14,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So in order to protect your mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.14,0:08:08.30,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.30,0:08:09.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.06,0:08:11.28,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.28,0:08:12.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.43,0:08:13.92,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.37,0:08:15.64,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.99,0:08:17.50,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.50,0:08:19.11,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.11,0:08:20.39,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.14,0:08:22.64,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.14,0:08:23.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He's become totally stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.92,0:08:24.18,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.76,0:08:26.37,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.37,0:08:27.78,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.78,0:08:28.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:31.17,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure, a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.17,0:08:32.14,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.77,0:08:35.20,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.61,0:08:39.58,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We went to canvas the hotel \NYuichi-san was staying at.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.32,0:08:42.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? You found her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.78,0:08:47.11,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She's still staying at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.96,0:08:48.71,Hotel,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Beika Business Hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.11,0:08:48.71,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,According to her...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.30,0:08:57.02,DCItalic,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.39,0:08:59.65,DCItalic,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.65,0:09:03.21,DCItalic,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. I wasn't \Nlooking where I was going.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.21,0:09:04.69,DCItalic,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Um, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.03,0:09:09.67,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,The time displayed on the phone she \Npicked up was approximately ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.13,0:09:16.07,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Additionally, the hotel employee who \Nhappened to pass by witnessed the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.35,0:09:19.94,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So he has multiple people \Nbacking up his alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.94,0:09:20.58,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.06,0:09:27.48,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,So I can leave now, right? \NMy alibi has been verified.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.03,0:09:30.07,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.07,0:09:31.84,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll give you a ride home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.01,0:09:34.34,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,No, thank you. More importantly...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.92,0:09:41.29,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never forget the humiliation I suffered \Nwhile being treated like a murder suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.76,0:09:43.22,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Clear the way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.22,0:09:44.54,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.18,0:09:49.52,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We came up empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.70,0:09:52.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but it's for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.59,0:09:53.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.52,0:09:59.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It would be tragic if one brother killed \Nthe other out of concern for his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.36,0:10:03.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, if we were wrong about him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.74,0:10:06.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's the guy Takagi is after.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.76,0:10:09.33,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Chiba, get in touch with Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.33,0:10:10.13,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.66,0:10:13.91,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The well-built man in his thirties.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.01,0:10:17.88,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,This guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.60,0:10:21.41,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. This is the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.41,0:10:22.76,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's definitely him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.39,0:10:26.27,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was asking around about Eiji-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.82,0:10:30.99,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but could I borrow this video?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.99,0:10:34.65,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. I'll get it ready for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.65,0:10:36.28,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.57,0:10:39.91,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Oh, Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.55,0:10:45.25,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I just finished checking some convenience \Nstore security camera footage for the man's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.25,0:10:47.10,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to bring it to the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.19,0:10:50.08,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,This is him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.08,0:10:50.79,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.11,0:10:52.90,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,This is Takase-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.36,0:10:55.90,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What? You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.90,0:10:57.67,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.67,0:10:59.76,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,His name is Takase Rintaro-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:04.43,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,He was my student back when \NI taught grade school.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.67,0:11:06.43,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Your old student?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.76,0:11:10.19,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Is this him, then? Did he kill Eiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.19,0:11:12.36,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,No. Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.36,0:11:14.94,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.72,0:11:18.82,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I was treated as a suspect \Nbecause of this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.09,0:11:24.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,W-We still don't know if he did it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.45,0:11:25.83,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.83,0:11:26.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.96,0:11:32.96,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Rintaro-kun was rowdy and \Ncaused a lot of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.62,0:11:35.96,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,But at heart, he was a good kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.34,0:11:40.47,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,He's not someone who could've \Nkilled another person.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.21,0:11:42.34,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.57,0:11:46.57,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Right? Why would Rintaro-kun kill Eiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.57,0:11:47.97,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,He has no reason to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.39,0:11:52.48,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So, have you met with Takase-san recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.84,0:11:57.48,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, last week at the \Nhosp—in the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.73,0:12:01.69,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What? Did you exchange addresses \Nor contact information then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.69,0:12:02.49,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.79,0:12:07.99,DCMain,YASUKO,0000,0000,0000,,He just said he was working at a \Nconstruction site near Hinode Pier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.68,0:12:27.10,Rintaro,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Takase Rintaro (32) \NConstruction Site Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.87,0:12:26.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Takase-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.99,0:12:27.71,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.17,0:12:32.52,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're Takase Rintaro-san, correct? \NGraduated from Haido Elementary School One.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.79,0:12:35.23,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,What if I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.74,0:12:41.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We're the police. Could we have \Na few minutes of your time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.88,0:12:46.55,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Wait for me at the pier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.55,0:12:49.85,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go ask my foreman for his permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.63,0:12:57.79,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't even surprised that \Nthe police suddenly showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.79,0:13:01.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He was smirking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.78,0:13:05.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And he didn't even ask why we were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.88,0:13:09.05,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He must've been expecting the police to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.23,0:13:22.57,DCItalic,ANNOUNCE,0000,0000,0000,,The water taxi for Asakusa is departing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.70,0:13:30.14,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Kadowaki Yasuko-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.14,0:13:32.87,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, of course I remember her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.33,0:13:36.36,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,I was a rowdy kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.83,0:13:40.14,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,She scolded me all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.40,0:13:44.39,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I hated her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.41,0:13:49.51,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,But that was twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.89,0:13:54.52,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You've been asking around the neighborhood \Nabout the Kadowaki family recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.93,0:13:58.36,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was last week that I ran into her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.36,0:14:00.51,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to know how she was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.51,0:14:02.02,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,I felt nostalgic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.26,0:14:07.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who suddenly feels nostalgic \Nabout someone they hated?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.56,0:14:08.53,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.09,0:14:13.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Takase-san, did you know that \NKadowaki Yasuko-san's younger son
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.53,0:14:18.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Kadowaki Eiji-san was killed last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.54,0:14:21.42,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,What? Her son was killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.55,0:14:27.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We came to talk to you as \Npart of the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.24,0:14:29.51,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.80,0:14:34.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So, Takase-san, where were \Nyou at ten last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.01,0:14:38.17,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. You think I did it, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.17,0:14:43.94,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,But if I wanted revenge, wouldn't I \Ngo after Kadowaki-sensei directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.22,0:14:47.57,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I kill her son?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.86,0:14:52.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A parent's greatest treasure is their \Nchildren, no matter how old they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.57,0:14:58.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you wanted to make her sad \Nby taking the life of her son.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.99,0:15:04.96,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. The police have put \Na lot of thought into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.96,0:15:07.96,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,How informative.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.94,0:15:12.05,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.58,0:15:17.41,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Last night around ten, I was \Nin the middle of a three hour
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.41,0:15:21.81,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,all you can drink session in Nebada.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.81,0:15:22.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.69,0:15:29.95,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I remember him well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.94,0:15:29.95,Brewery,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Three Hours ¥3330 \NAll You Can Eat & Drink!! \NNebada Brewery
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.29,0:15:32.45,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,He was sitting in that corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.82,0:15:36.51,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,He was facing the wall and kept \Nshouting about fighting spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.08,0:15:38.87,DCItalic,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Spirit, spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.87,0:15:44.38,DCItalic,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Ten katsu skewers and a large beer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.30,0:15:47.34,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,He probably went to the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.34,0:15:50.38,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,but aside from that, he was eating \Nand drinking the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.66,0:15:53.21,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what time that was?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.63,0:15:58.14,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was three hours \Nstarting just after eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.61,0:16:01.66,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to check our security cameras?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.66,0:16:04.14,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,They're only installed \Nat the entrance, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.83,0:16:06.96,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,You said around eight, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.96,0:16:09.17,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.72,0:16:11.78,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,It's this guy in the loud Hawaiian shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.00,0:16:14.20,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's definitely Takase.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.20,0:16:17.50,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,The time is 8:01 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.02,0:16:20.59,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,And three hours later...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.05,0:16:25.49,DCMain,TAKASI,0000,0000,0000,,He's leaving the restaurant after 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.79,0:16:35.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? He has an alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.71,0:16:36.55,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.96,0:16:43.31,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We were able to confirm that he was at a bar \Nin Nebada from eight to 11, just like he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.31,0:16:44.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.88,0:16:51.84,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,I told you so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.84,0:16:54.03,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.62,0:16:58.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that way. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.88,0:17:02.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But then who did?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.92,0:17:04.91,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,How would I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.91,0:17:09.42,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it your job to figure that out? Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.65,0:17:11.42,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.49,0:17:20.30,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm leaving now. \NGood luck with your job.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.88,0:17:22.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.17,0:17:26.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Megure here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.22,0:17:29.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? A fire at the \NKadowaki family residence?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.06,0:17:43.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.83,0:17:45.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's completely destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.52,0:17:49.12,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What about them? Where's the Kadowaki family?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.12,0:17:50.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.53,0:17:53.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're at that ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.01,0:17:59.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.86,0:18:02.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.59,0:18:04.81,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What about your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.64,0:18:09.99,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,They just took her away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.99,0:18:11.82,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to determine \Nthe cause of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.42,0:18:16.63,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.29,0:18:22.83,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,So that was your destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.77,0:18:30.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.65,0:18:33.61,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.28,0:18:42.40,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes there's nothing you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.84,0:18:48.15,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Inspector, I'll be leaving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.27,0:18:55.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.92,0:19:00.24,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm terribly sorry to ask at this time, \Nbut could you tell us what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.74,0:19:03.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,For your late mother's sake, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.85,0:19:04.74,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.25,0:19:11.25,Box,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Haido West Third Street Police Box
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.05,0:19:12.70,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,When the fire broke out, I was sleeping \Nin my room on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.16,0:19:17.88,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it's because I'd been questioned by \Nthe police, but I had a terrible headache.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.96,0:19:23.39,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,So by the time I realized something \Nwas amiss, it was a sea of fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.45,0:19:28.39,DCItalic,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Mom! Are you there, Mom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.14,0:19:32.32,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,It was all I could do to save myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.66,0:19:39.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It may be a coincidence, but I can't believe \Nhe lost his mother right after his brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.45,0:19:42.39,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.18,0:19:48.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichi-san, can you think of anyone \Nwho might have resented you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.62,0:19:50.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and the rest of the Kadowaki family?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.91,0:19:56.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Another one of your family \Nmembers died today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:20:00.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's too \Nmuch of a coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.55,0:20:03.19,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's not wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.91,0:20:06.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.03,0:20:09.17,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's a possibility. We should confirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.17,0:20:11.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.42,0:20:13.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Yuichi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.74,0:20:17.37,DCMain,YUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,No. I can't think of anyone like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.59,0:20:28.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I know what he said, but check out everyone \Nassociated with the Kadowaki family tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.68,0:20:32.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,See if anyone hated that family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.62,0:20:33.41,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.99,0:20:36.46,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Mori-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.25,0:20:38.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You don't like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.69,0:20:41.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.23,0:20:45.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, Inspector, we should get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.05,0:20:45.91,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.91,0:20:47.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.34,0:20:48.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.58,0:20:52.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That Takase guy definitely did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.68,0:20:55.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? But when the fire happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.90,0:20:57.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The fire is unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.84,0:21:00.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about Eiji-san's murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.21,0:21:04.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That fire was just an \Nunfortunate coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.70,0:21:08.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that his behavior was unnatural.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.52,0:21:13.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't surprised at all that \Nthe police suddenly showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.04,0:21:16.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Or when he heard Kadowaki \NEiji-san was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.80,0:21:20.04,DCItalic,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,What? Her son was killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.31,0:21:22.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed so deliberate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.86,0:21:23.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.60,0:21:29.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He knew that Eiji-san had been murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.34,0:21:31.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.94,0:21:41.94,Brewery2,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Nebada Brewery
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.19,0:21:46.70,Brewery3,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Three Hours ¥3330 \NAll You Can Eat & Drink!! \NNebada Brewery
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.51,0:21:53.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But he has an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.44,0:21:57.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was taken off the \Nsuspect list as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.15,0:22:01.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He must've used some kind of trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.67,0:22:07.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I, Mori Kogoro, swear on my \Nname that I'll expose him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.76,0:22:14.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't think the Kadowaki family \Nresidence fire was a total coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.60,0:22:19.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if that's true, then these two cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.13,0:22:22.42,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How in the world are they connected?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.05,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.30,0:23:49.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,9:08 to 10:35.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.46,0:23:51.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's about an hour and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.09,0:23:56.62,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,You were just saying how I could've \Nkilled him, too, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.62,0:23:59.04,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,What proof do you have that I did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.82,0:24:02.36,DCMain,TAKASE,0000,0000,0000,,You get in trouble at school, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.36,0:24:03.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.75,0:24:06.04,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.34,0:24:08.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:15.05,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Mystery-Solving Water Taxi \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.68,0:24:14.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The \NMystery-Solving Water Taxi, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.07,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Fireworks
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.63,0:24:33.02,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.59,0:24:34.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Fireworks!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.99,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.14,0:24:36.01,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}These two cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.01,0:24:37.20,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There's just no connection between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.20,0:24:38.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}As if obscured by smoke...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.02,0:24:39.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The truth is hazy.
